<title>USA: ICN, case ends in mistrial.</title>
<headline>ICN, case ends in mistrial.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1996-08-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>A mistrial has been declared in a shareholder suit against ICN Pharmaceuticals Inc that alleged the company made false and misleading statements about its anti-viral drug Virazole, lawyers in the case said on Thursday.</p>
<p>Daniel Berger, one of the shareholders' lead lawyers, said his clients would seek a new trial. The mistrial was declared on Wednesday after the Manhattan federal jury was deadlocked after a week of deliberations.</p>
